The cookie ID in each DoubleClick cookie is essential to these applications.
For example, DoubleClick uses cookie IDs to keep a log of which ads show to which browsers.
When it's time to serve an ad to a browser, DoubleClick can use the browser's cookie ID to check which DoubleClick ads have already been delivered to that particular browser.
That's how DoubleClick avoids showing ads the user has already seen.

In the same way, cookie IDs allow DoubleClick to log conversions related to ad requests—such as when a user views a DoubleClick ad and later uses the same browser to visit the advertiser's website and make a purchase.
DoubleClick cookies contain no personally identifiable information. Sometimes the cookie contains an additional identifier that is similar in appearance to the cookie ID.
This identifier is used to identify an ad campaign to which a user was exposed previously; but no personally identifiable information is stored by DoubleClick in the cookie.
Opting out If a user opts out using the Ads Settings , the unique DoubleClick cookie ID on the user's browser is overwritten with the phrase "OPT_OUT".
